10:43.033 --> 10:44.267
I do not understand that.

10:44.333 --> 10:45.633
-Yeah, that one I thought...
-It's called magic.

10:45.933 --> 10:47.867
JONES: <i>I still consider myself a student,</i>

10:47.933 --> 10:51.000
<i>but people do look to me</i>
<i>for techniques that I've devised</i>

10:51.067 --> 10:53.167
<i>and my handling of coin magic.</i>

10:53.433 --> 10:56.533
Not only am I excited
about being on <i>Penn &amp; Teller: Fool Us,</i>

10:56.600 --> 10:58.600
but I'm really looking
for the opportunity

10:58.667 --> 11:00.867
to share my magic
on a grander scale.

11:05.933 --> 11:09.833
This next magician is known
for his close-up magic with coins.

11:09.933 --> 11:11.000
I met him earlier today.

11:11.067 --> 11:12.467
I couldn't make heads or tails of him.

11:12.533 --> 11:15.200
Let's see if you can.
Please welcome Mr. Eric Jones,

11:15.267 --> 11:16.500
ladies and gentlemen.

11:18.267 --> 11:22.167
Tonight, I'm gonna share
something that's very dear to my heart.

11:22.233 --> 11:24.367
The problem with this illusion
that you're gonna see

11:24.433 --> 11:26.967
is that it's designed
for just a few people,

11:27.067 --> 11:29.167
and since there are so many
of you, I'd like to get

11:29.267 --> 11:31.467
a couple of volunteers to come
upstage to keep me honest,

11:31.533 --> 11:33.600
to make sure what everyone else
is about to see looks fair.

11:33.667 --> 11:35.100
(AUDIENCE CHEERING)

11:35.167 --> 11:36.533
Now, here's the thing, guys.

11:36.767 --> 11:39.933
If I choose you, you might think
that we have something worked out.

11:40.033 --> 11:41.733
So, if you don't mind, Penn,
would you mind

11:41.800 --> 11:43.300
-just choosing a couple people at random?
-Oh, sure.

11:43.367 --> 11:44.933
-Oh, boy. Oh, boy.
-(AUDIENCE CHEERING)

11:45.000 --> 11:46.567
Who have I got that'll...

11:46.800 --> 11:49.367
There's a big guy with both hands up.
Get on up here.

11:49.500 --> 11:50.867
-(AUDIENCE APPLAUDS)
-JONES: Yeah, one more.

