27:53.100 --> 27:55.733
-(AUDIENCE APPLAUDS)
-(MARK LAUGHS)

27:56.167 --> 27:57.533
-Great job.
-I'm here.

27:57.600 --> 27:59.967
I've got no idea how you did it,
but of course, I'm not a professional.

28:00.100 --> 28:01.867
Penn and Teller are
at the very top of their game,

28:01.933 --> 28:04.267
so let's ask Penn
what the duo thought.

28:04.333 --> 28:06.433
Well, if we were doing this trick,

28:07.067 --> 28:11.100
we would've done it
with, uh, cards that were marked,

28:11.167 --> 28:12.567
which you could've brought out
at the beginning...

28:12.633 --> 28:14.733
-Okay.
-And then it's very, very easy

28:14.800 --> 28:17.933
to do a blindfold peak
down your nose.

28:18.000 --> 28:22.133
And Teller and I love, love,
love blindfold peeks,

28:22.267 --> 28:25.400
and we love, love, love
marked cards.

28:26.300 --> 28:28.133
-But we don't think you did it that way.
-(AUDIENCE CHUCKLES)

28:28.200 --> 28:29.667
-Okay.
-We don't think you did it

28:29.733 --> 28:30.967
with a blindfold peek.

28:31.033 --> 28:33.067
We think you
actually did it tactilely.

28:33.133 --> 28:35.133
We think you were
actually feeling around.

28:35.300 --> 28:38.100
-Okay. Okay.
