29:44.400 --> 29:45.433
and I'm happy to perform
in front of you.

29:45.500 --> 29:46.633
And you did a great job.

29:46.733 --> 29:48.133
-Mark, you did a great job.
-Thank you.

29:48.200 --> 29:49.833
Super fun to watch,
and I loved being onstage with you.

29:49.933 --> 29:51.600
-Thank you.
-Mark Calabrese, ladies and gentlemen.

29:51.667 --> 29:53.433
-Great work. Nice to meet you, sir.
-(AUDIENCE APPLAUDS)

29:56.067 --> 29:58.400
Let's meet our next act.
We'll see if they've got what it takes.

30:02.533 --> 30:03.933
<i>My name is Paul Vigil.</i>

30:04.000 --> 30:05.567
I live in Las Vegas, Nevada.

30:05.733 --> 30:07.633
<i>Some people call me a magician,</i>

30:07.700 --> 30:09.567
<i>others a mind reader,</i>

30:09.633 --> 30:11.867
<i>and some perhaps maybe</i>
<i>even some kind of psychic.</i>

30:11.933 --> 30:13.067
(SNAPS FINGERS)

30:13.267 --> 30:15.367
<i>I grew up working</i>
<i>in a magic shop.</i>

30:15.433 --> 30:17.667
<i>Later on in my life,</i>
<i>I traveled around the world</i>

30:17.767 --> 30:20.033
-studying shamanic medicines.
-(SNAPS FINGERS)

30:20.200 --> 30:22.767
Once the curtains open
or they introduce me,

30:22.833 --> 30:26.133
that's like "once upon a time"
and all bets are off.

30:26.200 --> 30:29.000
Point to me a spot
like right here or right here or...

30:29.067 --> 30:33.167
Magic can have a consciousness
expanding effect on people.

30:33.233 --> 30:35.233
Look at that.
I just don't understand.

30:35.333 --> 30:36.567
-Mind blown.
-(PAUL LAUGHS)

30:36.700 --> 30:38.633
Part of what I'm interested
when I perform magic

30:38.700 --> 30:42.533
<i>is a moment that transcends</i>
<i>to help people know that mystery</i>

30:42.600 --> 30:46.367
is still alive where even smart people
will begin to doubt.

30:46.533 --> 30:48.300
(AUDIENCE CHEERING AND APPLAUDING)

30:51.033 --> 30:53.467
Will you please
welcome Paul Vigil?

30:53.900 --> 30:55.500
(ALL APPLAUDING)

31:02.467 --> 31:04.000
(MOUTHING) Oh, no.

31:04.467 --> 31:06.333
Can I ask you to ponder
something for a second?

31:06.400 --> 31:08.067
Do you think it's possible
that somebody,

31:08.133 --> 31:09.733
maybe even, like, myself,

31:09.800 --> 31:12.000
could stand here
in front of a group of strangers

31:12.067 --> 31:14.933
and predict exactly
what they may or may not do?

31:15.300 --> 31:17.033
-I'm gonna start with you, Penn.
-Okay.

31:17.133 --> 31:19.167
Now, please, I have some
specific statements

31:19.233 --> 31:21.567
with which I'm going to attempt
to influence you with.

31:21.633 --> 31:23.700
I'm gonna start with you
and I'll use a few more.

31:23.967 --> 31:26.433
The response that I want
from you is a single digit

31:26.500 --> 31:28.300
between zero and 10.

31:28.367 --> 31:31.533
Not zero and 10,
between zero and 10.

31:31.667 --> 31:33.900
Now, you know that I'm
attempting to influence you

31:33.967 --> 31:35.200
and my statement is,

31:36.033 --> 31:39.367
"One, two, buckle my shoe,

31:39.867 --> 31:43.133
"blank, four, unlock the door."

31:43.700 --> 31:46.800
(CHUCKLES) You know what the obvious digit
would be to put in this blank spot,

31:46.867 --> 31:48.800
but if you had a choice,
you would say?

31:48.967 --> 31:50.067
-Two.
-Two.

31:50.133 --> 31:51.500
I'll record that here for later.

31:53.333 --> 31:57.200
And perhaps this gentleman
right here in the red plaid?

31:57.367 --> 31:59.167
Again, we haven't set anything up,

31:59.233 --> 32:02.233
nobody's approached you
