32:02.333 --> 32:04.000
and I promise, if you listen carefully,

32:04.067 --> 32:05.400
I'll make you look good, all right?

32:05.467 --> 32:07.833
The statement I have
to influence you is,

32:08.033 --> 32:12.067
"Snow White and the blank Dwarfs."

32:12.400 --> 32:14.133
And the digit
you would give me is?

32:14.267 --> 32:15.267
-Four.
-Four.

32:15.333 --> 32:18.433
So, we're starting off
with a two and a four.

32:18.500 --> 32:19.900
And lastly, Teller.

32:20.167 --> 32:21.567
(AUDIENCE LAUGHS)

32:21.633 --> 32:23.767
Please, again, listen carefully.

32:23.833 --> 32:26.533
I don't think that these
statements will work on everybody,

32:26.633 --> 32:28.567
but I think that
this one will work with you.

32:28.633 --> 32:30.100
And the statement is,

32:30.500 --> 32:34.667
"Blank blind mice, see how they run."

32:35.167 --> 32:37.300
Please, can you hold up
some fingers for me?

32:37.500 --> 32:38.533
One.

32:38.600 --> 32:41.000
So, 241.

32:41.067 --> 32:42.900
Do you think there's any way
I could come out here

32:42.967 --> 32:44.933
and predict
that I would get this number,

32:45.000 --> 32:46.533
241?

32:47.000 --> 32:48.733
Please, can I have
you come up here, Penn?

32:48.800 --> 32:50.933
Let's give him a big round
of applause, please.

32:51.033 --> 32:52.533
(APPLAUDING)

32:54.067 --> 32:56.000
-How's it going today, pal?
-I'm doing very well, Paul.

32:56.067 --> 32:57.767
-How are you doing?
-Great, it's good to see ya.

32:57.833 --> 32:58.867
-Good to see you.
-Yeah!

32:58.933 --> 33:00.700
So, before I came out here tonight,

33:00.767 --> 33:02.300
-I took a business card.
-Uh-huh?

33:02.367 --> 33:04.667
I wrote three numbers
on this business card

33:04.733 --> 33:07.233
and then I put it somewhere
where everybody would know

33:07.300 --> 33:09.800
I wouldn't be able to touch it.
Any idea where that's at?

33:10.367 --> 33:11.500
Uh...

33:12.433 --> 33:15.867
Please, let me turn around.
Can you see that,

33:15.967 --> 33:17.867
pinned onto the back of my jacket?

33:17.933 --> 33:19.667
-Now, please don't touch it yet.
-Okay.

33:19.733 --> 33:21.400
That is legitimately
pinned on there

33:21.467 --> 33:23.167
and I am gonna have you verify that.

33:23.233 --> 33:24.767
-You can pull on that, please.
-Okay.

33:24.867 --> 33:25.867
It is pinned...

33:26.333 --> 33:27.833
-Yes?
-PENN: Very securely.

33:27.900 --> 33:29.267
PAUL: Go ahead,
you take the pin out.

33:29.333 --> 33:32.433
If I was to do that, they'd think
that's when I'm doing the sneaky stuff.

33:32.500 --> 33:34.767
And as you turn it over,
can you keep your thumb

33:34.833 --> 33:37.133
over those three numbers
that I've written on the other side?

33:37.233 --> 33:38.800
-Okay, I've taken it...
-I'd like you to be

33:38.867 --> 33:41.133
about surprised as everybody
else here, all right?

33:41.267 --> 33:42.633
-Open safety pin.
-Yeah.

33:42.700 --> 33:44.033
Dangerous, open safety pin.

33:44.100 --> 33:45.567
-(AUDIENCE LAUGHS)
-I don't trust you with this,

33:45.633 --> 33:47.067
and they don't trust me with that.

33:47.133 --> 33:48.567
-Okay.
-So, again, I asked you

33:48.633 --> 33:50.600
for a single digit between
zero and 10.

33:50.667 --> 33:52.767
-The number you gave me was a?
-A two, I believe.

33:52.833 --> 33:55.033
Two. Can you just slide over
to the first number,

33:55.100 --> 33:56.167
-and what number is...
-Two!

33:56.233 --> 33:57.933
-Yes!
-(AUDIENCE LAUGHS AND APPLAUDS)

33:58.000 --> 33:59.200
(PAUL LAUGHS)

33:59.267 --> 34:00.867
-Can you see that?
-No, wait, hold on.

34:00.967 --> 34:02.567
There's two chances
for me to mess up.

34:02.633 --> 34:05.300
Sir, the second digit
you gave me was a?

34:05.367 --> 34:07.367
-Four.
-What's the second number on that pa...

34:07.433 --> 34:09.533
Second number there is a four.

34:09.600 --> 34:10.766
(ALL CHEER AND APPLAUD)

34:10.833 --> 34:12.100
PENN: Two, four.

34:12.533 --> 34:15.800
And lastly, Teller, you could've named
any number in the universe.

34:15.867 --> 34:18.533
Well, any number
between zero and 10, yes?

34:19.067 --> 34:21.733
The number you gave me
was the number one.

34:21.867 --> 34:23.533
One and... Oh.

34:23.600 --> 34:24.833
PAUL: What's the last number
